<subSubSection id="C3017CB6FFEC187BFF5FCC1AFDE8F9B4" pageId="8" pageNumber="536" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA42F3DFFEC187BFF5FCC1AFDE8F9B4" blockId="8.[151,1436,1155,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis id="B96FF32FFFEC187BFF5FCC1AFE80FAE0" bold="true" box="[199,321,1377,1402]" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The only other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B54BEFFEC187BFDEECC19FD33FAE0" box="[630,754,1378,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pedaliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FF32FFFEC187BFDEECC19FD33FAE0" box="[630,754,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">Pedaliodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Andes of 
<collectingCountry id="F30C6FADFFEC187BFC2ECC1AFBE5FAE0" box="[950,1060,1377,1402]" name="Colombia" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">Colombia</collectingCountry>
with a wide HWD orange patch extending in the postdiscal-marginal area from the anal margin to M 
<number id="3DD33D1AFFEC187BFC2DCCFDFC00FA04" box="[949,961,1414,1438]" pageId="8" pageNumber="536" value="3.0">3</number>
is 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B54BEFFEC187BFC70CCFEFA88FA04" authority="Hewitson" authorityName="Hewitson" box="[1000,1353,1413,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pedaliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plotina">
<emphasis id="B96FF32FFFEC187BFC70CCFEFB7FFA07" box="[1000,1214,1413,1437]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">Pedaliodes plotina</emphasis>
(Hewitson)
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs only in the Eastern Cordillera and differs in being smaller, with a blunt FW apex, and in having no pale yellow or whitish dots on the orange patch. The ventral color pattern of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B54BEFFEC187BFC50CCB5FB81FA7F" box="[968,1088,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pedaliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philinae">
<emphasis id="B96FF32FFFEC187BFC50CCB5FB81FA7F" box="[968,1088,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">P. philinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nearly identical to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B54BEFFEC187BFA1FCCB5FEEEF990" authority="Thieme" authorityName="Thieme" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pedaliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polla">
<emphasis id="B96FF32FFFEC187BFA1FCCB5FF10F990" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">P. polla</emphasis>
Thieme
</taxonomicName>
, a species that occurs in the Eastern Cordillera of 
<collectingCountry id="F30C6FADFFEC187BFCC4CC8AFC0BF990" box="[860,970,1521,1546]" name="Colombia" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and the Venezuelan Cordillera de Mérida and has an all brown dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
